title: Sidewall, 1905–15
inscribed: Printed in right selvedge: "Pittsburg W. P. Co. New Brighton Pa. WP"
description:
Foliate treillage pattern with foliate medallions in the resulting diamond-shaped negative spaces. Background has a black and blue moiret pattern. Grounding is dark red. Printed in blues, yellows, blacks, reds, pinks, and white mica.
Printed in right selvedge: "Pittsburg W. P. Co. New Brighton Pa. WP"

tombstone.epitaph:
Sidewall, 1905–15.
1905–15. Machine-printed on paper, mica, liquid. Gift of Victorian Collectibles. 1979-91-603-a,b.
